<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h1>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Types_of_Orders_.28at_the_Exchange.29">Types of Orders (at the Exchange)</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Symbol</li>
<li>Buy, Sell</li>
<li>Market, Limit</li>
<li>Shares</li>
<li>Price (if Limit)</li>
</ul>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="The_Order_Book_.28recap.29">The Order Book (recap)</span></h2>
<p><pre>
* Ask   $100.10   100
* Ask   $100.05   500
* Ask   $100.00  1000
* Bid    $99.95   100
* Bid    $99.90    50
* Bid    $99.85    50
</pre></p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="How_Brokers_Connected_to_Exchanges">How Brokers Connected to Exchanges</span></h2>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Types_of_Orders_.28with_your_Broker.29">Types of Orders (with your Broker)</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Additional possibilities:
<ul><li><ul><li> Sell short (to open)
</li><li> Buy (to close)</li>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>
<li>More complex orders (stop limit)</li>
</ul>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Mechanics_of_Short_Selling">Mechanics of Short Selling</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Borrow the shares</li>
<li>Sell them</li>
<li>You now have:
<ul><li><ul><li> Asset: Cash
</li><li> Liability: Shares owed</li>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>
</ul>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Short_Selling_Example">Short Selling Example</span></h2>
<p></p>

